<item>
            <title>[LU-19113] cfs_delete_from_page_cache() should not unlock page</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19113</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;cfs_delete_from_page_cache()&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; had to be implemented because&#160; &lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;delete_from_page_cache()&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Kernel external is no longer available in recent Kernels, this has started with upstream Kernel v5.16-rc4 and has been addressed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16292&quot; title=&quot;ERROR: modpost: &amp;quot;delete_from_page_cache&amp;quot; undefined&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16292&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16292&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and fixed in associated Gerrit&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/49069&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;#49069&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking more closely to&#160;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;cfs_delete_from_page_cache()&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; code :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
/**
 * delete_from_page_cache is not exported anymore
 */
#ifdef HAVE_DELETE_FROM_PAGE_CACHE
#define cfs_delete_from_page_cache(page)&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; delete_from_page_cache((page))
#&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; inline void cfs_delete_from_page_cache(struct page *page)
{
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!page-&amp;gt;mapping)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; LASSERT(PageLocked(page));
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; get_page(page);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; unlock_page(page);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* on entry page is locked */&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (S_ISREG(page-&amp;gt;mapping-&amp;gt;host-&amp;gt;i_mode)) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; generic_error_remove_folio(page-&amp;gt;mapping, page_folio(page));
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; loff_t lstart = page-&amp;gt;index &amp;lt;&amp;lt; PAGE_SHIFT;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; loff_t lend = lstart + PAGE_SIZE - 1;


&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; truncate_inode_pages_range(page-&amp;gt;mapping, lstart, lend);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; lock_page(page);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; put_page(page);
}
#endif &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and also to other places where&#160;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;generic_error_remove_folio()&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt; is also being called, in both Lustre and Kernel, I have strong assumptions that page should not be unlocked prior to call it..., this may cause a race where page-&amp;gt;mapping may become NULL !&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will cook a patch soon in this direction.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
